1
00:00:04,109 --> 00:00:04,976
‎PREVIOUSLY ON <i>‎TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

2
00:00:05,043 --> 00:00:06,778
You didn't do anything wrong.

3
00:00:06,845 --> 00:00:10,415
So why do you
have to think of yourself as trash?

4
00:00:10,482 --> 00:00:11,316
It's frustrating.

5
00:00:11,382 --> 00:00:14,619
Are you still in contact with your family?

6
00:00:14,686 --> 00:00:16,621
<i>We had promised to meet and talk</i>

7
00:00:16,688 --> 00:00:19,791
<i>for the first time in a while,</i>
<i>but then that thing with Tomoki happened…</i>

8
00:00:19,858 --> 00:00:22,160
-Say…
-Yukanai!

9
00:00:22,227 --> 00:00:24,262
Please send that to your wife.

10
00:00:24,329 --> 00:00:26,631
<i>Tell her that this is</i>
<i>your current workplace.</i>

11
00:00:26,698 --> 00:00:29,300
<i>Ask her to come and see it sometime.</i>

12
00:00:30,101 --> 00:00:31,002
Sora

13
00:00:32,103 --> 00:00:33,538
hasn't been able to go to school yet.

14
00:00:34,105 --> 00:00:35,673
I want

15
00:00:36,808 --> 00:00:37,642
to talk with Sora.

16
00:00:39,777 --> 00:00:41,112
I have to ask Sora first.

17
00:00:41,179 --> 00:00:42,680
Daddy.

18
00:00:47,485 --> 00:00:48,453
Hello.

19
00:00:48,953 --> 00:00:50,855
Daddy, come with me.

20
00:00:52,957 --> 00:00:54,993
-Maybe a little later.
-Hurry, okay?

21
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:56,594
‎Okay.

22
00:00:59,063 --> 00:01:00,698
You make them call you "Daddy"?

23
00:01:00,765 --> 00:01:02,700
-No…
-Then why?

24
00:01:03,801 --> 00:01:04,636
Well…

25
00:01:06,204 --> 00:01:07,672
I don't know why either.

26
00:01:11,509 --> 00:01:12,977
Look at this.

27
00:01:16,214 --> 00:01:17,382
I'll contact you again

28
00:01:17,448 --> 00:01:19,517
after asking Sora whether
he wants to see you or not.

29
00:01:20,485 --> 00:01:21,319
Thanks.

30
00:01:21,819 --> 00:01:22,754
Tatsuki!

31
00:01:22,820 --> 00:01:24,656
-Tatsuki, let's play <i>Mario Kart</i>.
-Tatsuki.

32
00:01:24,722 --> 00:01:25,557
I'll join later.

33
00:01:25,623 --> 00:01:27,258
-We need an opponent.
-Join us.

34
00:01:27,325 --> 00:01:28,426
Okay, I'll be there.

35
00:01:28,493 --> 00:01:30,461
-Hurry.
-I got it.

36
00:01:31,429 --> 00:01:32,297
They're a handful, huh.

37
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:37,435
Kind of.

38
00:01:38,536 --> 00:01:39,370
Bye.

39
00:01:48,246 --> 00:01:51,783
So… how did it go?

40
00:01:54,752 --> 00:01:56,554
She said she'll tell Sora
that I want to see him.

41
00:01:58,223 --> 00:01:59,724
I'm glad to hear that.

42
00:02:00,425 --> 00:02:03,928
I felt kind of bad,
thinking that maybe I had done something

43
00:02:04,562 --> 00:02:05,997
out of line.

44
00:02:06,998 --> 00:02:09,867
Well, I'm glad I got to talk to her.

45
00:02:17,442 --> 00:02:18,977
NATIONAL MATHEMATICS COMPETITION
FINAL QUESTION

46
00:02:19,043 --> 00:02:20,411
Thanks for waiting, Umine.

47
00:02:20,478 --> 00:02:21,346
Sorry.

48
00:02:22,413 --> 00:02:24,182
Daddy, do you know how to solve this?

49
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:26,184
Why am I "Daddy"?

50
00:02:30,188 --> 00:02:32,056
Never mind. What do you need help with?

51
00:02:33,024 --> 00:02:34,859
It's a practice question
for the math competition.

52
00:02:34,926 --> 00:02:37,061
Let's see.

53
00:02:37,629 --> 00:02:39,030
Whoa, this is hard.

54
00:02:39,597 --> 00:02:41,132
You're this advanced?

55
00:02:41,899 --> 00:02:43,635
I don't know how to solve this at all.

56
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:49,874
I think I got it.

57
00:02:56,547 --> 00:02:58,883
Ta-da!

58
00:02:58,950 --> 00:03:00,652
Good day.

59
00:03:00,718 --> 00:03:02,287
I'm the witch,

60
00:03:02,353 --> 00:03:04,455
-Riri!
-Hey, Riri.

61
00:03:04,522 --> 00:03:07,058
We have to hurry or we'll be late
for the School of Magic.

62
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:09,160
-Give me one minute.
-Let's fly to school.

63
00:03:09,227 --> 00:03:10,662
Riri, you can't!

64
00:03:10,728 --> 00:03:11,696
What?

65
00:03:12,497 --> 00:03:14,332
Don't take Daddy away!

66
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,401
You call him "Daddy"?

67
00:03:17,001 --> 00:03:19,170
-You're so weird.
-I'm not weird.

68
00:03:19,237 --> 00:03:20,071
Stop.

69
00:03:20,138 --> 00:03:22,006
Forget you.

70
00:03:23,441 --> 00:03:24,275
Umine.

71
00:03:24,942 --> 00:03:25,843
Are you okay?

72
00:03:31,816 --> 00:03:34,319
-Who wants to vote for the picnic?
-Me!

73
00:03:34,385 --> 00:03:36,354
Raise your hand.

74
00:03:37,989 --> 00:03:39,957
You're all good to go now.

75
00:03:40,024 --> 00:03:42,794
-Thanks, Ajicchan.
-You're welcome.

76
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,095
-Let's go, Daddy.
-Okay.

77
00:03:44,162 --> 00:03:45,263
Votes for the flea market?

78
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:47,365
-Me!
-Wow, this many votes?

79
00:03:47,432 --> 00:03:49,300
There are so many votes for this.

80
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:52,003
Don't lower your hands.
Keep your hands up.

81
00:03:52,503 --> 00:03:53,504
You voted for the picnic?

82
00:03:54,305 --> 00:03:55,306
Picnics are fun.

83
00:03:55,373 --> 00:03:57,742
Results of the final votes are in.

84
00:03:57,809 --> 00:04:00,812
Saturday's Fun Day is a tie between
the flea market and the picnic.

85
00:04:01,379 --> 00:04:02,814
No way!

86
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,615
-What should we do?
-Flea market.

87
00:04:04,682 --> 00:04:06,784
Picnic would be so much better.

88
00:04:06,851 --> 00:04:08,152
Let's do both.

89
00:04:08,219 --> 00:04:09,153
Wow.

90
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:10,855
It's a fierce battle.

91
00:04:10,922 --> 00:04:13,825
I have lots of clothes to get rid of,
so a flea market would be great!

92
00:04:13,891 --> 00:04:15,593
How about selling
roasted sweet potatoes again?

93
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:18,629
Nice. Let's make a profit,
and use it for food expenses here.

94
00:04:19,130 --> 00:04:21,132
How will they decide what to do?

95
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:22,834
Should we choose with rock-paper-scissors?

96
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,435
Rock-paper-scissors?

97
00:04:24,502 --> 00:04:26,137
Who will represent each side?

98
00:04:26,204 --> 00:04:28,606
-Good question.
-The rep on my side better win.

99
00:04:28,673 --> 00:04:29,540
Hey.

100
00:04:30,108 --> 00:04:31,275
-Hey, Daiya.
-It's Daiya.

101
00:04:31,342 --> 00:04:32,744
Daiya, great timing.

102
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:35,346
You can help us out.

103
00:04:35,413 --> 00:04:36,481
Daiya.

104
00:04:36,547 --> 00:04:38,182
What should we do on Fun Day?

105
00:04:38,249 --> 00:04:39,484
Picnic or flea market?

106
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:40,818
Which one do you choose?

107
00:04:40,885 --> 00:04:41,953
What?

108
00:04:42,787 --> 00:04:45,556
Please.

109
00:04:48,559 --> 00:04:49,861
Flea market of course.

110
00:04:49,927 --> 00:04:51,829
Hooray!

111
00:04:51,896 --> 00:04:53,164
Yay!

112
00:04:54,999 --> 00:04:56,901
-Bye.
-See you.

113
00:04:56,968 --> 00:04:59,137
-What should we sell at the flea market?
-Umine,

114
00:04:59,203 --> 00:05:00,571
be careful on your way back.

115
00:05:01,372 --> 00:05:02,407
See you tomorrow, Daddy.

116
00:05:06,544 --> 00:05:08,279
-Bye.
-Bye.

117
00:05:08,346 --> 00:05:09,180
-Hello.
-Hey.

118
00:05:09,747 --> 00:05:11,649
How's it going, Daddy?

119
00:05:14,118 --> 00:05:15,420
Stop that.

120
00:05:15,486 --> 00:05:16,421
WHAT TO DO ON FUN DAY
FLEA MARKET

121
00:05:16,487 --> 00:05:18,156
-Oh, they decided on the flea market?
-Yes.

122
00:05:18,222 --> 00:05:20,958
Please put up any items
you no longer use for sale.

123
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,729
I wonder if anyone would take
the rope we used for tug-of-war?

124
00:05:25,596 --> 00:05:26,964
I highly doubt

125
00:05:27,031 --> 00:05:28,433
anyone would want that rope.

126
00:05:28,499 --> 00:05:30,501
That thing takes up a lot of space.

127
00:05:30,568 --> 00:05:31,769
I bet.

128
00:05:32,937 --> 00:05:34,539
Mr. Tatsuki,

129
00:05:34,605 --> 00:05:36,407
should we contact
Umine and Riri's guardians

130
00:05:36,474 --> 00:05:38,643
regarding today's incident?

131
00:05:39,877 --> 00:05:41,112
Yeah, since she got hurt.

132
00:05:41,179 --> 00:05:42,847
They got in a fight?

133
00:05:42,914 --> 00:05:43,915
Yeah.

134
00:05:43,981 --> 00:05:47,151
They got into an argument,
fighting over Mr. Tatsuki.

135
00:05:48,386 --> 00:05:50,788
-You're so popular.
-It's not like that.

136
00:05:50,855 --> 00:05:54,358
Lately, Umine has been
overly attached to Mr. Tatsuki.

137
00:05:54,425 --> 00:05:57,295
Today she was even calling him "Daddy."

138
00:05:58,529 --> 00:06:00,298
I wonder if something happened at home.

139
00:06:01,098 --> 00:06:03,401
Should we put a stop to it
before it becomes a habit?

140
00:06:03,468 --> 00:06:06,137
There might be a reason behind it, though.

141
00:06:06,737 --> 00:06:07,705
A reason?

142
00:06:10,007 --> 00:06:12,043
Maybe we should focus
on trying to understand

143
00:06:12,109 --> 00:06:14,045
Umine's feelings right now.

144
00:06:14,111 --> 00:06:14,946
Okay.

145
00:06:15,746 --> 00:06:18,382
Tatsuki, there's something
I want you to try out.

146
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:20,818
Sure.

147
00:06:20,885 --> 00:06:22,854
FUJINAGA

148
00:06:36,367 --> 00:06:37,802
I met your dad yesterday.

149
00:06:41,172 --> 00:06:42,006
He said

150
00:06:42,573 --> 00:06:44,342
he wants to talk with you.

151
00:06:46,410 --> 00:06:47,945
He wants to apologize to you.

152
00:06:50,882 --> 00:06:51,883
What do you want to do?

153
00:07:04,262 --> 00:07:06,964
I'm very sorry
about what happened yesterday.

154
00:07:07,031 --> 00:07:09,934
It's all right. How's her injury?

155
00:07:10,001 --> 00:07:11,569
Yes, she's totally fine.

156
00:07:12,136 --> 00:07:14,572
More importantly,
what about the other child?

157
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:15,907
She's okay too.

158
00:07:15,973 --> 00:07:17,308
What a relief.

159
00:07:18,142 --> 00:07:20,945
-I apologize for all the trouble.
-No problem.

160
00:07:22,013 --> 00:07:23,214
Wanna go to the atelier?

161
00:07:24,949 --> 00:07:25,816
Let's go.

162
00:07:26,817 --> 00:07:27,818
Bye.

163
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:32,490
She was never the type to get into fights.

164
00:07:33,824 --> 00:07:35,359
From your perspective,

165
00:07:35,426 --> 00:07:37,728
have you noticed
any changes with her recently?

166
00:07:38,396 --> 00:07:40,998
No, nothing comes to mind.

167
00:07:41,866 --> 00:07:43,334
I see.

168
00:07:43,401 --> 00:07:45,603
We'll make sure to keep an eye on her.

169
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:47,338
Thank you.

170
00:07:52,743 --> 00:07:54,078
What are we going to do?

171
00:07:54,779 --> 00:07:55,746
Today,

172
00:07:56,247 --> 00:07:57,915
we should have some fun using buttons.

173
00:07:58,482 --> 00:08:00,918
-Buttons?
-Yeah. Look at this.

174
00:08:01,919 --> 00:08:02,954
Ta-da.

175
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:04,155
These are all buttons?

176
00:08:04,221 --> 00:08:05,189
Yup.

177
00:08:05,256 --> 00:08:07,892
Choose the buttons you like
from among these,

178
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:10,328
and paste them onto the paper.

179
00:08:12,697 --> 00:08:13,564
How?

180
00:08:14,532 --> 00:08:15,633
Let's see…

181
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,403
Let's start by picking out a button
that reminds you of yourself,

182
00:08:19,971 --> 00:08:22,640
and also the ones that remind you

183
00:08:22,707 --> 00:08:25,309
of your family and friends around you.

184
00:08:25,810 --> 00:08:28,079
Which one should I choose?

185
00:08:28,145 --> 00:08:29,814
You can choose whatever you want.

186
00:08:45,496 --> 00:08:46,364
I want an example.

187
00:08:46,964 --> 00:08:48,466
-An example?
-Yeah.

188
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:50,835
An example, huh…

189
00:08:52,036 --> 00:08:54,338
I wonder if I still have the ones
we made before.

190
00:08:55,906 --> 00:08:57,441
How about these

191
00:08:58,209 --> 00:08:59,543
as examples?

192
00:09:00,778 --> 00:09:01,612
This is interesting.

193
00:09:02,413 --> 00:09:03,714
It is, isn't it?

194
00:09:09,086 --> 00:09:10,788
It comes in a lot of different sizes.

195
00:09:12,723 --> 00:09:14,291
There are all sorts of patterns too.

196
00:09:15,526 --> 00:09:16,360
This one is cute.

197
00:09:17,094 --> 00:09:17,995
Yeah, it's cute.

198
00:09:18,496 --> 00:09:20,665
Keep choosing whichever one you like.

199
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,335
I'll choose these for myself.

200
00:09:25,302 --> 00:09:26,671
They remind you of yourself?

201
00:09:28,673 --> 00:09:29,940
Nice.

202
00:09:30,007 --> 00:09:32,977
Then how about the buttons
for the people around you?

203
00:09:36,013 --> 00:09:37,915
Let's see…

204
00:09:40,618 --> 00:09:41,652
This reminds me of Daddy.

205
00:09:42,887 --> 00:09:43,721
Yeah.

206
00:10:11,415 --> 00:10:12,750
I wonder if this is right.

207
00:10:15,152 --> 00:10:16,554
There’s no right or wrong answer.

208
00:10:17,054 --> 00:10:18,923
Just go with whatever feels right to you.

209
00:10:21,892 --> 00:10:23,661
I'm not sure what feels right.

210
00:10:30,468 --> 00:10:33,404
Some buttons are lined up neatly,

211
00:10:33,471 --> 00:10:35,573
and others are kind of scattered.

212
00:10:38,409 --> 00:10:40,511
-It's a nice contrast.
-Really?

213
00:11:19,784 --> 00:11:20,885
All done.

214
00:11:21,485 --> 00:11:22,386
Very well done.

215
00:11:29,026 --> 00:11:30,761
What is it, Riri?

216
00:11:37,368 --> 00:11:38,435
Umine,

217
00:11:39,603 --> 00:11:41,038
I'm sorry about yesterday.

218
00:11:45,276 --> 00:11:47,111
I'm sorry too.

219
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:51,615
I'm proud of you guys
for apologizing and making up.

220
00:11:53,651 --> 00:11:55,186
Let's play with stuffed animals.

221
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:00,024
Let's go.

222
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:01,792
Bye, Daddy.

223
00:12:02,626 --> 00:12:03,828
Bye.

224
00:12:03,894 --> 00:12:04,995
Let's go.

225
00:12:06,297 --> 00:12:07,598
Okay then…

226
00:12:28,219 --> 00:12:30,588
It seems like they made up.

227
00:12:31,222 --> 00:12:33,858
Riri had been bottling up
her own stress too.

228
00:12:35,025 --> 00:12:36,427
Is that right?

229
00:12:36,493 --> 00:12:40,431
You know, Umine has been
studying a lot lately, right?

230
00:12:40,497 --> 00:12:42,433
So I think Riri felt a little lonely.

231
00:12:42,499 --> 00:12:45,603
Yeah, Umine is solving
really difficult math problems.

232
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:49,506
Yeah. She's good enough to compete
in the national mathematics competition.

233
00:12:51,442 --> 00:12:53,344
It's only natural for her dad
to get fired up.

234
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:54,879
-This one?
-Yeah.

235
00:12:54,945 --> 00:12:57,882
What brought Umine to Yukanai
in the first place?

236
00:12:58,449 --> 00:13:00,584
She was way ahead
of her class academically,

237
00:13:00,651 --> 00:13:02,519
which made things awkward
with the other kids,

238
00:13:02,586 --> 00:13:03,754
and so she couldn't fit in.

239
00:13:04,688 --> 00:13:07,224
Wow, I've never
heard of such a thing before.

240
00:13:07,791 --> 00:13:08,692
It's interesting, huh?

241
00:13:14,565 --> 00:13:16,333
I brought the rope
to sell at the flea market.

242
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,301
Where should I put it?

243
00:13:17,368 --> 00:13:20,137
It would be in the way if you put it here.

244
00:13:20,204 --> 00:13:21,939
Can you leave it in the playroom?

245
00:13:22,006 --> 00:13:23,974
-Okay, got it.
-Thank you.

246
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:25,442
Oh no.

247
00:13:25,509 --> 00:13:26,911
Whoa!

248
00:13:26,977 --> 00:13:27,811
Are you all right?

249
00:13:27,878 --> 00:13:29,346
I'm all right.

250
00:13:29,413 --> 00:13:30,648
YUKANAI

251
00:13:30,714 --> 00:13:34,618
This button here represents Umine herself.

252
00:13:34,685 --> 00:13:37,922
The buttons that are lined up neatly,
represent her family.

253
00:13:41,125 --> 00:13:42,993
This button in the center is you, right?

254
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,628
Yes, that seems to be the case.

255
00:13:44,695 --> 00:13:47,398
I think the buttons all around
represent everyone at Yukanai.

256
00:13:48,165 --> 00:13:50,768
There's quite a contrast between
her home and Yukanai.

257
00:13:50,834 --> 00:13:51,669
Yes.

258
00:13:54,405 --> 00:13:56,640
How was Umine while she was
working on this?

259
00:13:57,241 --> 00:13:59,043
Let's see…

260
00:14:01,278 --> 00:14:03,213
I told her to work on it
however she liked.

261
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:06,583
But she asked to see an example,
and was worried about doing it "right."

262
00:14:08,485 --> 00:14:11,322
Since Umine is good at math,

263
00:14:11,388 --> 00:14:14,191
maybe she was looking for
a single, definitive answer.

264
00:14:14,258 --> 00:14:15,859
-That makes sense.
-Yeah.

265
00:14:15,926 --> 00:14:17,861
You might be right.

266
00:14:17,928 --> 00:14:19,029
Excuse me.

267
00:14:19,096 --> 00:14:20,531
This is in the way in the playroom,

268
00:14:20,597 --> 00:14:22,199
so can I leave this here?

269
00:14:22,266 --> 00:14:23,467
Sorry, Shi-chan.

270
00:14:23,534 --> 00:14:25,869
I don't want that here either.

271
00:14:25,936 --> 00:14:26,870
So, um…

272
00:14:26,937 --> 00:14:28,339
It's okay temporarily, right?

273
00:14:28,405 --> 00:14:29,840
-Seriously?
-Sorry.

274
00:14:29,907 --> 00:14:30,975
I'll leave it in the corner.

275
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:32,242
-Right here.
-Sorry.

276
00:14:32,309 --> 00:14:34,078
-In this corner.
-Fine.

277
00:14:34,144 --> 00:14:36,213
What's the situation with Umine's family?

278
00:14:37,581 --> 00:14:39,616
Umine's dad is a single father.

279
00:14:39,683 --> 00:14:42,619
From my conversation with her dad,
I got the impression

280
00:14:42,686 --> 00:14:44,154
that he is kind and proper.

281
00:14:44,221 --> 00:14:46,390
But she's calling Tatsuki "Daddy," right?

282
00:14:46,457 --> 00:14:47,591
Yeah.

283
00:14:49,259 --> 00:14:51,261
Is she not getting enough attention
from her dad?

284
00:14:51,862 --> 00:14:54,732
Like, maybe her dad is usually
so busy with work

285
00:14:54,798 --> 00:14:56,867
that they don't get to talk much.

286
00:14:58,702 --> 00:15:02,639
Well, Umine hasn't really reached out
with a call for help just yet,

287
00:15:02,706 --> 00:15:04,408
but let's keep a close eye on things.

288
00:15:04,475 --> 00:15:05,309
-Okay.
-Okay.

289
00:15:18,322 --> 00:15:20,791
Are you done with your homework?

290
00:15:21,525 --> 00:15:22,493
‎Yeah.

291
00:15:22,593 --> 00:15:25,129
Now I'm thinking about
what to sell at the flea market.

292
00:15:31,802 --> 00:15:32,636
How about this?

293
00:15:35,873 --> 00:15:38,275
You're a big girl now,
so you don't need this, right?

294
00:15:53,123 --> 00:15:55,392
YUKANAI

295
00:15:55,459 --> 00:15:58,162
SATURDAY FUN DAY
YUKANAI FLEA MARKET

296
00:15:58,228 --> 00:16:00,164
YUKA-TAMASHI

297
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:04,868
-What do you want?
-I want a bag.

298
00:16:04,935 --> 00:16:05,769
A bag?

299
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:07,371
This is cute. You want it?

300
00:16:07,438 --> 00:16:09,406
-You have so many books.
-We sure do.

301
00:16:09,473 --> 00:16:11,308
-Wow.
-All of these are five yen each.

302
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:12,476
That's so cheap.

303
00:16:12,543 --> 00:16:13,544
Want roasted sweet potatoes?

304
00:16:13,610 --> 00:16:14,878
Yes.

305
00:16:14,945 --> 00:16:16,380
-Two please.
-Okay.

306
00:16:16,447 --> 00:16:18,482
Thank you.

307
00:16:18,549 --> 00:16:20,951
Welcome, welcome.

308
00:16:21,018 --> 00:16:22,986
Come one, come all!

309
00:16:23,053 --> 00:16:25,489
Today's featured item is this rope.

310
00:16:25,556 --> 00:16:28,525
It's a symbol of unity,
and a token of victory.

311
00:16:28,592 --> 00:16:30,294
The undisputed star of the Sports Day.

312
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,563
And would you believe it,
this is only 800 yen.

313
00:16:32,629 --> 00:16:33,897
What would we use that for?

314
00:16:33,964 --> 00:16:35,132
For tug-of-war.

315
00:16:35,199 --> 00:16:37,534
-And when would we ever do that?
-What?

316
00:16:37,601 --> 00:16:38,669
-Let's go.
-Hold on.

317
00:16:38,735 --> 00:16:40,104
Hey, buy this.

318
00:16:41,071 --> 00:16:42,739
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

319
00:16:42,806 --> 00:16:44,875
-Thank you.
-Come again.

320
00:16:44,942 --> 00:16:45,776
-Bye.
-Tatsuki.

321
00:16:45,843 --> 00:16:46,777
Bye.

322
00:16:46,844 --> 00:16:48,645
Hey, if it isn't Rui!

323
00:16:49,346 --> 00:16:51,115
-It's really busy.
-Yeah.

324
00:16:51,181 --> 00:16:53,584
It's been a while. How've you been?

325
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:54,651
Okay, I guess.

326
00:16:56,386 --> 00:16:58,088
You have a good eye.

327
00:16:58,155 --> 00:17:00,958
It says "ask" for the price,
but how much is it?

328
00:17:01,525 --> 00:17:03,260
Thank you for asking.

329
00:17:04,127 --> 00:17:05,696
-It's 500 yen.
-That's so cheap.

330
00:17:06,763 --> 00:17:08,065
I want this.

331
00:17:08,132 --> 00:17:09,466
-This?
-Yeah.

332
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:11,768
-It's cute, isn't it?
-Yeah, it sure is.

333
00:17:12,369 --> 00:17:13,637
It's another rabbit.

334
00:17:15,372 --> 00:17:16,707
They can play with it together.

335
00:17:16,773 --> 00:17:17,608
Yeah.

336
00:17:18,242 --> 00:17:19,643
All right, let's see…

337
00:17:24,615 --> 00:17:25,716
Umine.

338
00:17:26,383 --> 00:17:28,051
You're really selling that stuffed animal?

339
00:17:28,986 --> 00:17:29,820
‎Yeah.

340
00:17:30,587 --> 00:17:31,522
I see.

341
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:35,926
You used to play with that a lot.

342
00:17:37,794 --> 00:17:39,196
But I'm a big girl now.

343
00:17:40,664 --> 00:17:41,565
I see.

344
00:17:47,337 --> 00:17:48,238
Tatsuki.

345
00:17:49,373 --> 00:17:51,942
Taking entrance exams is meaningless
unless you ace it.

346
00:18:01,385 --> 00:18:02,352
What is it?

347
00:18:03,854 --> 00:18:05,756
I hope you win the math competition.

348
00:18:08,158 --> 00:18:08,992
I'll win a medal.

349
00:18:13,096 --> 00:18:14,531
Shi-chan.

350
00:18:14,598 --> 00:18:16,433
Shi-chan.

351
00:18:20,737 --> 00:18:22,105
Hello.

352
00:18:22,172 --> 00:18:23,073
Hello.

353
00:18:24,608 --> 00:18:26,276
That's for high school students.

354
00:18:26,343 --> 00:18:29,513
Lately, Umine started working
on high school math too.

355
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:31,582
-What?
-It's still just the basics, though.

356
00:18:32,783 --> 00:18:34,751
-She's already at high school level?
-Yes.

357
00:18:34,818 --> 00:18:37,754
She just keeps solving math problems
all on her own.

358
00:18:38,355 --> 00:18:39,523
That's amazing.

359
00:18:42,526 --> 00:18:44,194
Umine, let's play.

360
00:18:44,695 --> 00:18:45,829
Let's go to the magical forest.

361
00:18:46,396 --> 00:18:48,632
Sorry, I'm working on math right now.

362
00:18:48,699 --> 00:18:50,167
That's too bad.

363
00:18:52,169 --> 00:18:53,003
Then maybe later.

364
00:18:53,937 --> 00:18:54,771
Let's go.

365
00:18:55,405 --> 00:18:57,307
Bye. Good luck.

366
00:18:57,374 --> 00:18:59,042
-Let's go.
-Bye.

367
00:18:59,843 --> 00:19:00,744
You don't want to go?

368
00:19:02,713 --> 00:19:04,181
I have to finish all this today.

369
00:19:04,681 --> 00:19:05,649
Really?

370
00:19:06,350 --> 00:19:07,718
You're so studious.

371
00:19:08,685 --> 00:19:10,954
It's the home stretch
before the competition.

372
00:19:11,455 --> 00:19:12,289
I see.

373
00:19:24,534 --> 00:19:26,336
I think you miscalculated right here.

374
00:19:27,704 --> 00:19:28,872
‎What?

375
00:19:33,477 --> 00:19:36,413
But you used the correct formula.

376
00:19:38,382 --> 00:19:39,316
Why…?

377
00:19:39,816 --> 00:19:40,884
How did this happen?

378
00:19:42,352 --> 00:19:43,954
You'll get it right next time.

379
00:19:44,655 --> 00:19:46,723
It's pointless if it's not perfect.

380
00:19:51,995 --> 00:19:54,798
Umine, it's time for cram school.
Let's get ready to go.

381
00:19:58,902 --> 00:19:59,736
What's this?

382
00:20:04,675 --> 00:20:05,942
I'm sorry.

383
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:10,947
Why did you make a mistake?

384
00:20:12,582 --> 00:20:15,052
You want to win the gold medal, right?

385
00:20:20,424 --> 00:20:23,193
I'm always telling you
to review your answers, aren't I?

386
00:20:25,929 --> 00:20:26,963
Yes.

387
00:20:30,634 --> 00:20:33,103
We'll be going now.

388
00:20:42,245 --> 00:20:43,246
Umine.

389
00:20:45,082 --> 00:20:46,283
See you tomorrow.

390
00:20:54,858 --> 00:20:56,760
<i>When I'm looking at Umine</i>

391
00:20:57,327 --> 00:20:59,329
it reminds me of my own childhood.

392
00:21:00,297 --> 00:21:01,932
Your childhood?

393
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:06,470
When I was around her age,
I was also doing nothing but studying.

394
00:21:09,005 --> 00:21:09,940
Um…

395
00:21:12,943 --> 00:21:14,745
I think there's a possibility

396
00:21:15,979 --> 00:21:19,449
that Umine is being subjected
to "tiger parenting."

397
00:21:20,417 --> 00:21:22,586
-Tiger parenting?
-Yes.

398
00:21:22,652 --> 00:21:24,955
For example, making a child study
for a long time

399
00:21:25,021 --> 00:21:26,890
and depriving them of playtime,

400
00:21:27,391 --> 00:21:30,394
or reprimanding them for mistakes
more than is necessary

401
00:21:30,460 --> 00:21:32,696
would certainly raise such suspicions.

402
00:21:33,263 --> 00:21:35,332
Some parents are focused
on their child's education.

403
00:21:36,199 --> 00:21:39,603
Yes, and that's why it's difficult
to know where to draw the line.

404
00:21:40,771 --> 00:21:44,207
Umine is working hard
of her own free will, and I understand

405
00:21:44,274 --> 00:21:46,543
the desire to live up
to your parents' expectations,

406
00:21:46,610 --> 00:21:48,178
because I felt the exact same way.

407
00:21:48,245 --> 00:21:50,013
I also agree

408
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:53,216
that Umine is studying of her own accord.

409
00:21:53,917 --> 00:21:54,851
But I also think

410
00:21:54,918 --> 00:21:58,555
she's being cornered into thinking that
she has no choice but to push herself

411
00:21:58,622 --> 00:22:00,490
in order to live up to expectations.

412
00:22:03,493 --> 00:22:04,494
There are times

413
00:22:05,061 --> 00:22:06,730
when parents themselves aren't even aware

414
00:22:06,797 --> 00:22:08,698
that they are pressuring their kids.

415
00:22:09,266 --> 00:22:10,367
Is that right?

416
00:22:12,202 --> 00:22:14,104
She might be unknowingly
pushing herself too hard

417
00:22:14,604 --> 00:22:16,706
and causing her emotional state
to become unstable.

418
00:22:18,708 --> 00:22:23,213
That might also be the reason why

419
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:25,982
she started calling you "Daddy."

420
00:22:29,886 --> 00:22:32,422
Okay, I'll keep a close eye on her.

421
00:22:41,331 --> 00:22:43,567
I'm naming her Usa-chan.

422
00:22:44,468 --> 00:22:45,936
Usa-chan.

423
00:22:47,237 --> 00:22:48,705
Usa-chan.

424
00:22:49,539 --> 00:22:50,974
-It's so cute.
-I just made it.

425
00:22:51,041 --> 00:22:53,677
Wow. This part

426
00:22:53,743 --> 00:22:55,378
is so colorful.

427
00:22:55,445 --> 00:22:56,780
Yeah, it's colorful.

428
00:23:04,020 --> 00:23:06,490
She's all dressed up.

429
00:23:06,990 --> 00:23:09,226
Look at this.

430
00:23:12,929 --> 00:23:13,930
What's the matter?

431
00:23:16,266 --> 00:23:18,268
It's nothing.

432
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:24,641
It's okay to quit, you know.

433
00:23:28,845 --> 00:23:30,514
Something got in my eye, that's all.

434
00:23:32,048 --> 00:23:32,949
I'm okay.

435
00:23:33,450 --> 00:23:34,518
Let's be friends.

436
00:23:34,584 --> 00:23:38,121
-I'm all dressed up. It's cute, right?
-I'm so jealous.

437
00:23:38,188 --> 00:23:40,490
I want to dress up fancy too.

438
00:23:40,991 --> 00:23:42,058
Then I'll help you out.

439
00:23:42,125 --> 00:23:43,894
Hooray. Thanks.

440
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,896
-Come this way.
-I can use this.

441
00:24:00,477 --> 00:24:01,478
<i>Tatsuki,</i>

442
00:24:02,112 --> 00:24:04,014
why are you crying?

443
00:24:04,848 --> 00:24:06,850
You can't have dinner
until you finish that.

444
00:24:08,218 --> 00:24:09,052
Yes.

445
00:24:11,054 --> 00:24:12,255
Crying

446
00:24:12,889 --> 00:24:14,591
isn't going to solve anything, you know.

447
00:24:27,804 --> 00:24:30,006
Wake up. Let's get started.

448
00:24:31,241 --> 00:24:32,275
Okay.

449
00:24:32,342 --> 00:24:33,176
GRADES

450
00:24:33,243 --> 00:24:34,844
No matter how hard you try,

451
00:24:34,911 --> 00:24:37,714
taking entrance exams is meaningless
unless you ace it.

452
00:24:40,216 --> 00:24:44,321
If you want to be a person of value,
produce results.

453
00:25:01,137 --> 00:25:03,239
YUKANAI

454
00:25:03,306 --> 00:25:05,141
Do it in 30 seconds.

455
00:25:05,208 --> 00:25:06,209
Make it 30 seconds.

456
00:25:06,276 --> 00:25:08,111
I can do it in 20 seconds.

457
00:25:08,178 --> 00:25:10,847
-Really, 20 seconds?
-I can do 17 seconds.

458
00:25:15,085 --> 00:25:17,320
Are you sleeping well at night?

459
00:25:19,689 --> 00:25:20,523
‎Yeah.

460
00:25:21,091 --> 00:25:21,925
When's your bedtime?

461
00:25:24,761 --> 00:25:25,829
Daddy,

462
00:25:26,563 --> 00:25:29,065
my whole life is on the line right now.

463
00:25:30,066 --> 00:25:32,535
This isn't the time to be
sleeping or playing.

464
00:25:33,236 --> 00:25:34,604
I understand that, but…

465
00:25:35,639 --> 00:25:36,773
Daddy,

466
00:25:37,574 --> 00:25:38,675
are you on my side?

467
00:25:39,643 --> 00:25:40,510
Of course.

468
00:25:41,111 --> 00:25:41,945
Then

469
00:25:42,779 --> 00:25:43,813
please stay quiet.

470
00:25:53,289 --> 00:25:56,760
What made you come to like math?

471
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,969
I guess it's because

472
00:26:06,036 --> 00:26:08,571
it was the thing I was best at
among all my lessons.

473
00:26:12,208 --> 00:26:13,977
Even though I get scolded if I mess up.

474
00:26:15,879 --> 00:26:16,713
By your dad?

475
00:26:22,852 --> 00:26:24,654
How does he scold you?

476
00:26:30,493 --> 00:26:31,828
He tells me,

477
00:26:32,595 --> 00:26:33,997
"No dinner until you get it right."

478
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,201
Then you'll get hungry, right?

479
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:43,673
But it's my own fault
for not being able to solve it.

480
00:26:47,243 --> 00:26:49,079
Sometimes you just want
to have fun, right?

481
00:26:50,714 --> 00:26:52,615
But I have to get good grades…

482
00:26:56,586 --> 00:26:58,088
Otherwise, even you

483
00:26:59,022 --> 00:27:00,523
will start to hate me.

484
00:27:01,357 --> 00:27:04,227
Don't say things like that.
I will never hate you.

485
00:27:05,829 --> 00:27:06,663
Really?

486
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:08,298
Yes.

487
00:27:09,699 --> 00:27:13,169
You have every right
to think more about yourself.

488
00:27:15,505 --> 00:27:17,073
About myself?

489
00:27:19,909 --> 00:27:21,411
Tatsuki, let's play <i>Mario Kart</i>.

490
00:27:21,911 --> 00:27:22,779
Let's play.

491
00:27:23,513 --> 00:27:25,081
No, don't go!

492
00:27:27,817 --> 00:27:29,552
-Ask Soya--
-Listen here, Umine!

493
00:27:29,619 --> 00:27:32,489
Tatsuki isn't yours to hog, you know.

494
00:27:33,223 --> 00:27:34,991
‎-Let's go.
‎-No!

495
00:27:35,058 --> 00:27:36,593
-Don't take him!
-Stop.

496
00:27:36,659 --> 00:27:38,027
-What?
-Okay, that's enough.

497
00:27:41,197 --> 00:27:42,165
‎Sorry.

498
00:27:50,473 --> 00:27:54,110
Umine, it's almost time
for your cram school.

499
00:27:55,812 --> 00:27:57,046
It's already that time, huh?

500
00:28:00,083 --> 00:28:01,251
Daddy.

501
00:28:02,218 --> 00:28:03,153
What is it?

502
00:28:06,422 --> 00:28:07,423
Daddy,

503
00:28:08,491 --> 00:28:11,427
you'll always stay by my side
no matter what, right?

504
00:28:16,666 --> 00:28:20,570
If you have any problems at home,
you can contact me.

505
00:28:24,674 --> 00:28:26,576
TATSUKI

506
00:28:39,422 --> 00:28:40,757
I'M AWAKE
YOU'RE STILL AWAKE?

507
00:28:40,824 --> 00:28:42,325
<i>You're still awake?</i>

508
00:28:43,459 --> 00:28:45,728
<i>Yeah, because I'm not finished yet.</i>

509
00:28:50,099 --> 00:28:52,001
<i>Don't push yourself too hard.</i>

510
00:28:55,271 --> 00:28:58,374
<i>Dad says now is the time</i>
<i>to really buckle down.</i>

511
00:29:02,579 --> 00:29:04,581
<i>Did you eat?</i>

512
00:29:06,416 --> 00:29:07,951
<i>My stomach hurts.</i>

513
00:29:16,226 --> 00:29:18,461
<i>You really need to get some proper rest.</i>

514
00:29:27,370 --> 00:29:31,040
<i>If I don't win a medal, Dad will be sad.</i>

515
00:29:38,348 --> 00:29:39,749
<i>You're doing it for your dad?</i>

516
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:42,886
<i>What is it</i>
<i>that you really want to do, Umine?</i>

517
00:29:51,327 --> 00:29:52,195
Umine.

518
00:29:54,030 --> 00:29:55,098
Coming.

519
00:29:59,669 --> 00:30:01,204
<i>Dad is calling me.</i>

520
00:30:15,551 --> 00:30:16,786
Ms. Shizuku.

521
00:30:16,853 --> 00:30:18,755
Good morning.

522
00:30:18,821 --> 00:30:22,091
You're up early.
Usually you're still asleep at this time.

523
00:30:22,592 --> 00:30:24,827
About Umine…

524
00:30:25,461 --> 00:30:26,296
Yes?

525
00:30:27,230 --> 00:30:28,898
I was thinking it might be a good idea

526
00:30:29,399 --> 00:30:31,467
to have her dad come here once
so we can talk.

527
00:30:32,302 --> 00:30:34,437
Talk about what?

528
00:30:35,004 --> 00:30:36,806
Regarding his approach
to Umine's education.

529
00:30:37,974 --> 00:30:39,676
I was thinking that maybe we should

530
00:30:39,742 --> 00:30:41,678
have a discussion to see
if his current approach

531
00:30:42,178 --> 00:30:43,780
is truly in her best interests.

532
00:30:45,014 --> 00:30:48,484
If she's really being subjected
to tiger parenting,

533
00:30:48,551 --> 00:30:51,254
I would certainly
want to do something to address it.

534
00:30:52,055 --> 00:30:55,158
But this is a really
difficult issue, isn't it?

535
00:30:56,492 --> 00:30:57,327
What do you mean?

536
00:30:58,328 --> 00:31:01,030
At this stage, what we can do

537
00:31:01,097 --> 00:31:02,598
is kind of limited.

538
00:31:04,233 --> 00:31:06,402
You want to leave this alone
and do nothing?

539
00:31:08,004 --> 00:31:10,073
You're the one who's always saying

540
00:31:10,139 --> 00:31:12,809
that we shouldn't meddle
in family matters.

541
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:14,577
You don't care what happens to Umine?

542
00:31:15,578 --> 00:31:17,780
-That's not what I mean.
-Never mind.

543
00:31:18,715 --> 00:31:19,782
I'll handle it myself.

544
00:31:19,849 --> 00:31:21,351
What are you going to do?

545
00:31:21,417 --> 00:31:23,052
I'll take Umine away from her dad.

546
00:31:23,119 --> 00:31:25,922
-You can't do that!
-What if it all becomes too late?

547
00:31:25,989 --> 00:31:27,790
-Like I said--
-Hey, let's calm down.

548
00:31:27,857 --> 00:31:29,959
You guys are fighting
first thing in the morning?

549
00:31:31,527 --> 00:31:32,729
I'm sorry.

550
00:31:35,198 --> 00:31:37,500
I baked some financiers.
Do you guys want some?

551
00:31:38,468 --> 00:31:39,302
Here you go.

552
00:31:39,869 --> 00:31:42,005
Enjoy. One for you too.

553
00:31:42,071 --> 00:31:44,941
Nobody can stay angry
while they're eating something sweet.

554
00:31:45,008 --> 00:31:46,542
Come on, eat up.

555
00:31:46,609 --> 00:31:48,378
Whenever you get angry, eat a financier.

556
00:31:49,012 --> 00:31:49,846
Got it?

557
00:31:50,546 --> 00:31:51,381
Okay.

558
00:31:57,820 --> 00:31:59,322
As for the flea market the other day,

559
00:31:59,389 --> 00:32:01,691
the final accounting
ended up turning a profit,

560
00:32:01,758 --> 00:32:02,992
albeit just barely.

561
00:32:03,059 --> 00:32:05,428
-I knew we could count on you.
-Good job.

562
00:32:05,495 --> 00:32:08,431
Although the rope ended up not selling.

563
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,467
Where's Tatsuki?

564
00:32:12,168 --> 00:32:14,437
He's been on his phone for a while now.

565
00:32:15,004 --> 00:32:17,974
I think he's messaging with Umine.

566
00:32:18,041 --> 00:32:19,142
With Umine?

567
00:32:20,243 --> 00:32:21,611
It’s not really appropriate

568
00:32:21,677 --> 00:32:24,313
to communicate personally
outside of Yukanai,

569
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:25,515
right?

570
00:32:26,416 --> 00:32:27,917
Yeah, I don't recommend it.

571
00:32:28,818 --> 00:32:31,687
He’s completely preoccupied with Umine,
as if he's really her daddy.

572
00:32:31,754 --> 00:32:33,189
Yes.

573
00:32:33,256 --> 00:32:37,493
When I mentioned
the possibility of tiger parenting,

574
00:32:38,061 --> 00:32:41,197
he became even more involved
with her situation.

575
00:32:41,764 --> 00:32:43,132
I see.

576
00:32:51,641 --> 00:32:52,942
Hey there.

577
00:32:54,143 --> 00:32:56,079
-Oh, the meeting…
-No worries.

578
00:32:56,145 --> 00:32:57,346
It ended already.

579
00:32:58,448 --> 00:32:59,282
I'm sorry.

580
00:33:03,019 --> 00:33:03,953
You look like

581
00:33:05,588 --> 00:33:06,856
you're under a lot of pressure.

582
00:33:08,458 --> 00:33:09,292
Really?

583
00:33:11,094 --> 00:33:13,863
Tatsuki, why don't you give
button art a try too?

584
00:33:14,430 --> 00:33:15,565
Me?

585
00:33:16,065 --> 00:33:17,300
Um… why?

586
00:33:17,366 --> 00:33:19,001
Let's just do it.

587
00:33:20,069 --> 00:33:24,107
After all, you're also
a subject of my research.

588
00:33:24,173 --> 00:33:26,109
Sit down.

589
00:33:27,877 --> 00:33:30,246
I wonder what they're doing.

590
00:33:32,815 --> 00:33:34,750
Maybe it's art therapy.

591
00:33:36,352 --> 00:33:39,122
Professor Mikumo
is taking it upon himself to handle it?

592
00:33:39,822 --> 00:33:40,890
It's kind of rare.

593
00:33:41,891 --> 00:33:42,725
Yeah.

594
00:34:19,695 --> 00:34:22,098
How about something like this?

595
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,868
How did you feel while making this?

596
00:34:28,271 --> 00:34:29,739
Nothing in particular.

597
00:34:32,842 --> 00:34:36,679
It looked as though you were making it
with hesitation and uncertainty.

598
00:34:38,414 --> 00:34:39,982
You may be right.

599
00:34:40,850 --> 00:34:43,986
I, myself, wasn't even sure
what I was trying to make.

600
00:34:44,921 --> 00:34:46,222
I see.

601
00:34:48,424 --> 00:34:52,361
Lately, Umine has been relying on you
rather excessively, hasn't she?

602
00:34:53,329 --> 00:34:54,163
Yes.

603
00:34:59,502 --> 00:35:00,670
That’s…

604
00:35:04,106 --> 00:35:05,975
called "transference."

605
00:35:06,642 --> 00:35:09,579
Maybe she's unconsciously
projecting feelings

606
00:35:09,645 --> 00:35:11,614
she'd normally harbor toward her own dad,
onto you?

607
00:35:13,783 --> 00:35:15,051
That might be it.

608
00:35:16,319 --> 00:35:18,454
What concerns me even more, however,

609
00:35:18,521 --> 00:35:20,556
is the fact that right now

610
00:35:21,057 --> 00:35:22,358
you are…

611
00:35:27,230 --> 00:35:30,466
experiencing countertransference.

612
00:35:30,967 --> 00:35:34,337
COUNTERTRANSFERENCE

613
00:35:35,304 --> 00:35:36,505
Countertransference?

614
00:35:37,873 --> 00:35:39,742
Without even realizing it,

615
00:35:40,977 --> 00:35:42,612
you've become way too invested in her.

616
00:35:46,415 --> 00:35:47,717
When I see Umine,

617
00:35:48,451 --> 00:35:52,421
I'm reminded of myself when I was a child.
So I feel the need to do something.

618
00:35:53,456 --> 00:35:56,525
I understand how you feel,
but you should step back a little.

619
00:35:59,929 --> 00:36:00,896
Why?

620
00:36:00,963 --> 00:36:04,267
Exchanging messages with her
until this late,

621
00:36:04,333 --> 00:36:06,569
is really going a little too far.

622
00:36:07,303 --> 00:36:09,138
Then who is going
to look after her instead?

623
00:36:09,205 --> 00:36:11,540
-Who'll listen to her cries for help?
-Calm down.

624
00:36:11,607 --> 00:36:12,808
I am calm.

625
00:36:12,875 --> 00:36:14,343
Pull yourself together.

626
00:36:17,980 --> 00:36:19,849
If you lose your head over this,

627
00:36:20,449 --> 00:36:22,051
you won't be able to save her.

628
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:25,855
I know that.

629
00:36:32,728 --> 00:36:35,331
Take some time off work.

630
00:36:39,302 --> 00:36:40,603
I can't do that…

631
00:36:41,504 --> 00:36:43,272
This is a corporate mandate.

632
00:37:16,539 --> 00:37:18,941
I told him to take time off work
for a while.

633
00:37:20,776 --> 00:37:21,944
I see.

634
00:37:22,712 --> 00:37:25,414
But he doesn't really have
anywhere else to go, does he?

635
00:37:26,749 --> 00:37:28,017
Oh, right.

636
00:37:28,084 --> 00:37:29,385
I forgot he lives here.

637
00:37:30,786 --> 00:37:33,255
I'm sure he'll come back.

638
00:37:34,690 --> 00:37:36,625
You guys can go home now.

639
00:37:37,460 --> 00:37:38,394
Okay.

640
00:37:38,461 --> 00:37:39,895
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

641
00:37:39,962 --> 00:37:42,131
-Thank you.
-Bye.

642
00:38:03,152 --> 00:38:06,322
ANDO

643
00:38:21,637 --> 00:38:22,638
Sora,

644
00:38:23,539 --> 00:38:24,440
what's the matter?

645
00:38:29,445 --> 00:38:30,813
I'll meet with him.

646
00:38:35,785 --> 00:38:36,819
With your dad?

647
00:38:39,188 --> 00:38:40,523
I don't care either way.

648
00:38:58,174 --> 00:38:59,809
UMINE

649
00:38:59,875 --> 00:39:02,511
<i>Daddy, I'm tired.</i>

650
00:39:10,953 --> 00:39:11,987
I'm tired.

651
00:39:13,255 --> 00:39:15,090
It's just a little bit more.

652
00:39:15,858 --> 00:39:17,827
Finish that, and you can go to sleep.

653
00:39:19,061 --> 00:39:19,895
Yes.

654
00:39:35,845 --> 00:39:38,380
<i>You don't have to work hard</i>
<i>just to get praised by your dad.</i>

655
00:39:39,348 --> 00:39:41,917
<i>Just do whatever you enjoy.</i>

656
00:39:53,295 --> 00:39:58,033
YU
CAN YOU MAKE TIME TO MEET TOMORROW?

657
00:40:05,508 --> 00:40:06,509
Just a little more!

658
00:40:06,575 --> 00:40:08,244
-Just a little more!
-It's almost done.

659
00:40:08,310 --> 00:40:09,512
All right,

660
00:40:09,578 --> 00:40:11,247
it's done.

661
00:40:11,313 --> 00:40:12,915
There you go.

662
00:40:12,982 --> 00:40:14,683
-I want to go next.
-Be careful.

663
00:40:14,750 --> 00:40:16,385
-I'm going next.
-No, it's me.

664
00:40:16,452 --> 00:40:18,988
-Take turns, everyone.
-Keep climbing up.

665
00:40:19,054 --> 00:40:20,523
Go for it.

666
00:40:20,589 --> 00:40:21,824
-Are you okay?
-You can do it.

667
00:40:21,891 --> 00:40:24,894
-Good job.
-You did it.

668
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:27,796
The rope you couldn't sell
has a new life now.

669
00:40:29,765 --> 00:40:31,600
I'm glad it found a new home.

670
00:40:32,201 --> 00:40:34,003
Nice. Good job.

671
00:40:34,069 --> 00:40:36,772
Good job.

672
00:40:36,839 --> 00:40:38,374
-You can do it.
-Have you seen Tatsuki?

673
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:40,776
No, not yet.

674
00:40:40,843 --> 00:40:42,044
You can do it.

675
00:40:42,678 --> 00:40:44,146
I see.

676
00:40:44,213 --> 00:40:45,047
-Go for it.
-Okay.

677
00:40:57,026 --> 00:40:58,460
Welcome.

678
00:41:12,141 --> 00:41:13,375
It's been a while.

679
00:41:15,611 --> 00:41:18,581
He's working
at an alternative school right now.

680
00:41:19,114 --> 00:41:20,516
I went to visit the other day.

681
00:41:22,251 --> 00:41:24,753
There are all kinds of kids,
and sometimes it gets tough

682
00:41:25,254 --> 00:41:26,755
but I'm managing somehow.

683
00:41:28,457 --> 00:41:29,725
Excuse me.

684
00:41:35,464 --> 00:41:36,765
Please enjoy.

685
00:41:40,669 --> 00:41:41,670
How about you, Sora?

686
00:41:42,972 --> 00:41:44,273
How have things been lately?

687
00:41:54,984 --> 00:41:58,120
I feel terrible
about what I did to you, Sora.

688
00:42:00,589 --> 00:42:02,157
I acted selfishly,

689
00:42:02,658 --> 00:42:04,593
without ever stopping
to consider your feelings.

690
00:42:06,261 --> 00:42:08,030
I should've been right there by your side,

691
00:42:08,530 --> 00:42:10,332
as the one who understood you best.

692
00:42:12,568 --> 00:42:15,404
Instead, all I did was hurt you.

693
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:26,081
I'm really sorry.

694
00:42:36,825 --> 00:42:37,793
So?

695
00:42:43,432 --> 00:42:46,435
Must be nice for you,
having a new job and all,

696
00:42:48,504 --> 00:42:50,739
but I haven't even been able
to go back to school.

697
00:42:54,209 --> 00:42:55,611
Even if you can't go to school,

698
00:42:56,378 --> 00:42:59,481
-I'll support whatever you want to do--
-Shut up.

699
00:43:03,318 --> 00:43:05,154
Everything is all over now.

700
00:43:07,156 --> 00:43:08,557
All thanks to you.

701
00:43:15,764 --> 00:43:17,666
YUKANAI

702
00:43:22,071 --> 00:43:24,840
Answer that. It's your work, right?

703
00:43:33,782 --> 00:43:34,717
Excuse me.

704
00:43:43,525 --> 00:43:45,461
-Hello?
<i>-Mr. Tatsuki.</i>

705
00:43:46,428 --> 00:43:47,429
Um…

706
00:43:48,897 --> 00:43:49,998
Umine

707
00:43:50,065 --> 00:43:53,535
is in the atelier
and she's refusing to come out.

708
00:43:55,137 --> 00:43:57,473
<i>She told us to call you over right now.</i>

709
00:43:57,539 --> 00:44:00,309
I told her
that you're on leave for a while.

710
00:44:01,410 --> 00:44:04,146
Then she said, "But he promised

711
00:44:04,213 --> 00:44:06,648
that he’d always
stay by my side no matter what."

712
00:44:08,250 --> 00:44:09,218
Okay.

713
00:44:09,718 --> 00:44:11,086
I'll call you back.

714
00:44:27,970 --> 00:44:29,605
Sorry, I have to go.

715
00:44:38,947 --> 00:44:40,616
You didn't used to be like this.

716
00:44:42,251 --> 00:44:43,118
What?

717
00:44:46,355 --> 00:44:48,991
You never helped me when I needed it.

718
00:45:08,477 --> 00:45:10,212
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

719
00:45:10,279 --> 00:45:11,847
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita

